nhc_headline: ...HURRICANE HUNTER AIRCRAFT REPORT THAT GABRIELLE IS FARTHER EAST AND A LITTLE STRONGER THAN INDICATED IN THE PREVIOUS ADVISORY...
summary: ...HURRICANE HUNTER AIRCRAFT REPORT THAT GABRIELLE IS FARTHER EAST AND A LITTLE STRONGER THAN INDICATED IN THE PREVIOUS ADVISORY... As of 2:00 PM AST Sat Sep 20 the center of Gabrielle was located near 25.2, -58.7 with movement NW at 13 mph. The minimum central pressure was 996 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 65 mph.
